adqlParser.query
Interface ADQLOperand

All Superinterfaces:
ADQLObject
All Known Implementing Classes:
ADQLColumn, ADQLColumnAndMeta, ADQLConstantValue, ADQLFunction, AreaFunction, BoxFunction, CentroidFunction, CircleFunction, Concatenation, ContainsFunction, DistanceFunction, Exists, ExtractCoord, ExtractCoordSys, GeometryFunction, InFunction, IntersectsFunction, MathFunction, Operation, PointFunction, PolygonFunction, RegionFunction, SQLFunction, UCDFunction, UserFunction
public interface ADQLOperand
extends ADQLObject

This class is the generic definition of an operand which can be used as item of the clause SELECT or as "parameter" of a constraint.
Since this operand may be a SELECT's item it may have an alias (see the functions getAlias() and setAlias(String)). Indeed it may correspond to a numeric value and so it is possible to put a minus symbol in front of, to make negative the numeric value (example: -1.2, -_s_ra, ...).
